description:
&lt;p&gt;South London and Maudsley NHS Foundation Trust is seeking exceptional candidates to join our inpatient nursing teams within the borough of Lambeth. The posts are open to newly qualified, or soon to be newly qualified, RN&#39;s as well as experienced RN&#39;s. The role of an RN within our inpatients services involves being an effective member of the Multidisciplinary Team (MDT) and to be responsible for the development and facilitation of a patient centered approach to outstanding care: assessing, developing, implementing and evaluating the care needs of patients and their carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent preceptorship and support as well as training and career development offered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have excellent opportunities on a range of wards at Lambeth Hospital as well as the Maudsley Hospital:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Rosa Parks ward is a male acute ward at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Luther King ward is a male acute ward at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Nelson ward is a female acute ward at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-LEO (Lambeth Early Onset) ward is a mixed sex ward at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-THU (Tony Hillis Unit) ward is a rehabilitation ward at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Eden ward is a male Psychiatric Intensive Care Unit at Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-ES2 (Eileen Skellern) ward is a male ward at the Maudsley Hospital (SE5 8AZ)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Florence ward is a 15 bedded mixed acute inpatient unit which was originally opened in April 2020 as a Covid positive acute admission ward. Lambeth Hospital (SW9 9NU)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lambeth hospital is centrally located close to Stockwell, Brixton and Clapham North tube stations. The Maudsley Hospital is located in Denmark Hill, as is our Trust headquarters, which is less than 5 minutes from the train station (zone 2). We also provide services and operate across other locations, such as London boroughs of Croydon, Lambeth, Lewisham and Southwark; and substance misuse services for residents of Bexley, Lambeth, Greenwich and Wandsworth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisted candidates will be invited to interview on Friday 21st February 2020 at our Lambeth Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to ensuring our staff get the most out of their benefits package and understand the importance of a healthy work life balance. There is an extensive range of excellent benefits for you and your family. We want you to feel like you are part of a close knit team at SLaM. It’s important to us that you valued and appreciated and that are why we have a comprehensive benefits package on offer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of our benefits are highlighted here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generous pay, pensions and leave, &lt;/strong&gt;we offer a comprehensive pay, pensions and leave package which is dependent on the role and length of service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work life balance, &lt;/strong&gt;flexible working and support a range of flexible options, such as: part-time working and job sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Career development, &lt;/strong&gt;There are plenty of opportunities to progress your career and we support your development through a number of programmes such as mentoring, coaching, positive people management, collective leadership and other talent programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car lease, &lt;/strong&gt;our staff benefits from competitive deals to lease cars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accommodation, &lt;/strong&gt;our staff benefits from keyworker housing available which is available on selected sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NHS discounts, &lt;/strong&gt;with discounts up to 10% from a variety of well-known retail brands though Health Service Discounts website.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other benefits include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Counselling services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wellbeing events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long service awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to work scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Season ticket loan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Staff restaurants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJuliet MutamiriJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressjuliet.mutamiri@slam.nhs.ukTelephone number0203 2288621&lt;/p&gt;
